---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { identity } from "../config";
---

<Layout
  seo={{
    title: "Design | " + identity.name,
    description: "Design projects by Zayneb Cherif.",
    image: identity.logo,
  }}
>
  <section class="mt-10 max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 scroll-reveal">
    <h1 class="font-bold text-3xl mb-10 text-center">Design</h1>

    <div class="mb-16">
      <a href="https://arena-vis.vercel.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block overflow-hidden rounded-lg hover:opacity-95 transition-opacity">
        <img
          src="/design-arena-vis-v2.png"
          alt="Are.na Visualizer"
          class="w-full h-auto"
        />
      </a>

      <div class="mt-6">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Are.na Visualizer</h2>
        <p class="text-sm opacity-55 leading-relaxed mb-4">A visual explorer for Are.na channels — browse collections across multiple layout modes including grid, canvas, and disk views.</p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mb-4">
          <span class="skill-box">Tailwind CSS</span>
          <span class="skill-box">Are.na API</span>
          <span class="skill-box">TypeScript 5</span>
          <span class="skill-box">React 19</span>
          <span class="skill-box">Next.js 16</span>
          <span class="skill-box">Vercel</span>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <a
            href="https://arena-vis.vercel.app"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-sm opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity underline underline-offset-2"
          >Live site &rarr;</a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/zcher-20/arena-vis"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-sm opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity underline underline-offset-2"
          >GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mb-16" style="position:relative;">
      <a href="https://github.com/zcher-20/Film-Album" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="block overflow-hidden rounded-lg hover:opacity-95 transition-opacity">
        <img
          src="/design-film-album.png"
          alt="Film Album"
          class="w-full h-auto"
        />
      </a>

      <div class="mt-6" style="position:relative;">
        <span
          id="film-album-title"
          class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2 inline-block cursor-default"
          style="text-decoration-color:rgba(0,0,0,0.25);"
        >Film Album</span>
        <p class="text-sm opacity-55 leading-relaxed mb-4 mt-2">An interactive, scroll-driven photo gallery built with vanilla JavaScript. A single self-contained HTML file featuring a continuous depth-based carousel, real-time caption editing, and full client-side persistence.</p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-1.5 mb-4">
          <span class="skill-box">Vanilla JavaScript</span>
          <span class="skill-box">IndexedDB</span>
          <span class="skill-box">File API</span>
          <span class="skill-box">CSS Transforms</span>
          <span class="skill-box">Scroll Architecture</span>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <a
            href="https://github.com/zcher-20/Film-Album"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="text-sm opacity-60 hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity underline underline-offset-2"
          >GitHub &rarr;</a>
        </div>

        <!-- Engineering Note hovercard -->
        <div
          id="film-album-hovercard"
          class="design-hovercard"
          style="display:none;"
        >
          <p style="font-size:12px; color:#111; margin:0 0 8px; font-weight:700;">Engineering Note</p>
          <p style="font-size:11px; color:#555; margin:0; line-height:1.6;">The interface maps a tall scroll container to a sticky viewport, translating scroll offset into a continuous progress value that drives the entire visual state. Keeping the animation in a single rAF loop (rather than CSS transitions) allows every visual property to track scroll velocity smoothly and avoids the jank of competing transitions. The entire app ships as one portable HTML file with zero external requests.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<script is:inline>
  (function() {
    var trigger = document.getElementById('film-album-title');
    var card = document.getElementById('film-album-hovercard');
    if (!trigger || !card) return;
    var timer = null;
    function show() { clearTimeout(timer); if (window.innerWidth > 768) card.style.display = 'block'; }
    function hide() { timer = setTimeout(function() { card.style.display = 'none'; }, 150); }
    trigger.addEventListener('mouseenter', show);
    trigger.addEventListener('mouseleave', hide);
    card.addEventListener('mouseenter', show);
    card.addEventListener('mouseleave', hide);
  })();
</script>

<style>
  .skill-box {
    font-size: 10px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: transparent;
    color: #6b7280;
    font-family: inherit;
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .design-hovercard {
    position: absolute;
    left: calc(100% + 16px);
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    width: 260px;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid #e8e8e8;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    padding: 18px;
    z-index: 100;
    pointer-events: auto;
  }
</style>
